title: Guide for reproducible scientific analysis
text:
DOI



Guide for reproducible scientific analysis
To reproduce the figure results in publication on Theoretical and Applied Genetics Wang et al, 2023,
please do the following 4 steps:

Clone the repository to your local environment. Folder structure should look like this:

R_script
¦–Wang_2023_TAAG.Rproj
¦–README.md
¦–data
¦ °–Wang_et_al_TAAG_2023_physiological_parameter.rds
¦–result
¦ °–Networkdata
¦ ¦–si_layout_circle.csv
¦ °–t_layout_circle.csv
°–src
¦–Data_preparation.R
¦–Fig1_preparation.R
¦–Fig1_S1.R
¦–Fig2.R
¦–Fig2_prep_fun.R
¦–Fig2_S3_4_preparation.R
¦–Fig3.R
¦–Fig3_4_6_preparation.R
¦–Fig3_6_prep_fun.R
¦–Fig4.R
¦–Fig5.R
¦–Fig5_prep_fun.R
¦–Fig5_preparation.R
¦–Fig6.R
¦–FigS3.R
¦–FigS4.R
¦–TC_theme.R
°–TC_theme2.R
2. Go to , Please download the following data from Zenodo and place it to the data folder * Wang_et_al_TAAG_2022_output_trait.rds
3. Install R package toolStability by install.packages("toolStability").
4. Run with the Data_preparation.R to FigS4.R in an ascending manner (order as shown above).
Enjoy!!
Citation info:
Wang, T-C., Casadebaig, P., Chen, T-W. More than 1000 genotypes are required to derive robust relationships between yield, yield stability and physiological parameters: a computational study on wheat crop. Theor Appl Genet (2023). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00122-023-04264-7
